<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.237093>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. F. cusanicaformis sp. n. (A – C), F. granulocyta sp. n. (D – G), and Mesenchytraeus calyx sp. n. (H – K). F. cusanicaformis: A. Spermathecae. B. Coelomocytes. C. Sperm funnel. F. granulocyta: D. Oesophageal appendage. E. Coelomocytes. F. Spermatheca. G. Sperm funnel. Mesenchytraeus calyx: H. Brain of adult specimen. I. Sperm bundle. J. Spermatheca. K. Male copulatory organ (a = atrium; sd = sperm duct; ag = atrial glands; acg = accessory copulatory glands)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/237093/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.237095>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Micrographs of F. granulocyta sp. n. A. Brain. B. Chaetae, ventral view. C. Coelomocytes, type b. D. Male copulatory organs, ventral view. E. Sperm funnel (black arrow), male copulatory organ (white arrow), lateral view. F. Clitellar glands of holotype, ventral view; between the bursal slits (= pb) only granulocytes (white arrow); female pores marked with black arrows. G. Sperm funnel (white arrow) and adjacent nephridium; its adseptal origin of ectal duct marked with black arrow. H – I. Spermathecae; long ectal ducts marked with white arrows, ampullae marked with black arrows (pg = pharyngeal glands). A – D, G, H in vivo, E, F, I fixed, stained. Scale bars 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/237095/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

